<h1 id="cloud-platform-user-guide">Cloud platform user guide</h1><h2 id="using-this-guide">Using this guide</h2><p>To the left, you will see the top-level navigation items.</p>

<ul>
<li><strong>Concepts</strong>: High-level articles, e.g. &ldquo;What is Kubernetes?&rdquo;</li>
<li><strong>Tasks</strong>: Articles covering specific &ldquo;how to&rdquo; topics, e.g. &ldquo;How to deploy an
application&rdquo;</li>
<li><strong>Reference</strong>: Information such as Cloud Platform processes, and links to
external documentation resources</li>
<li><strong>Getting Help</strong>: How to get help if you can&rsquo;t find what you need in this
guide</li>
</ul>
<p>Click these to expand the corresponding section of the guide.</p>
<p>Currently, the vast majority of the information in the guide is in the &ldquo;Tasks&rdquo; section.</p>

<blockquote>
<p>Because of the way this guide is <a href="https://github.com/alphagov/tech-docs-template">published</a>, each of the
sections ends up as a single HTML page. Because of this, you might find
Cmd-F/Ctrl-F on the &ldquo;Tasks&rdquo; page more useful than the search box in the upper
left corner.</p>
</blockquote>
<h2 id="brand-new-to-kubernetes-the-cloud-platform">Brand new to Kubernetes/The Cloud Platform?</h2><p>The <a href="tasks.html#deploying-a-39-hello-world-39-application-to-the-cloud-platform">Deploying a Hello World application</a> tutorial is a good place to start.</p>
<h2 id="adding-to-the-guide">Adding to the guide</h2><p>If there&rsquo;s something missing, please either let us know and we&rsquo;ll add a new
article, or if you&rsquo;re comfortable writing one yourself, PRs will be gratefully
received. Details on how to get in touch are in the &ldquo;Getting Help&rdquo; section, and
the &ldquo;GithHub&rdquo; link at the top right will take you to the repository for this
guide.</p>
